replies.bodyText:
@droberts195 What you'll have to do is update the alias on all indices that have that alias simultaneously, like so:
POST _aliases
{
    "actions": [
        {
            "add": {
                "index": ".ml-annotations-1",
                "alias": ".ml-annotations-read",
                "is_hidden": true
            }
        },
        {
            "add": {
                "index": ".ml-annotations-2",
                "alias": ".ml-annotations-read",
                "is_hidden": true
            }
        }
    ]
}

Even though the action is add, you can use it to update aliases that already exist. This is a bit inconvenient, but it's somewhat of a limitation of the alias infrastructure, and we should be able to work around it by querying for the list of indices and alias points to and generating the update aliases list from that. Let me know if this would be troublesome for you/your team.

